In this article, Vice President Kamala Harris and President Joe Biden address the need for gun safety laws and police reform. They express their condolences to the families affected by recent tragedies, including the shooting in Uvalde, Texas. They emphasize the importance of creating a safe and inclusive America and call on Congress to pass the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act. President Biden signs an executive order that aims to promote accountability, raise standards, and modernize policing. The order includes measures such as creating a national law enforcement accountability database, banning chokeholds, and requiring federal agents to wear body cameras. The President and Vice President acknowledge the work that still needs to be done and emphasize the importance of unity and collective action.